formation, and a suite of merger simulations, we find that many of the\nobservational properties of NGC 4494 may be explained by formation in a\nrelatively recent gas-rich major merger. Complete studies of individual\ngalaxies incorporating a range of observational avenues and methods such as the\none presented here will be an invaluable tool for constraining the fine details\nof galaxy formation models, especially at large galactocentric radii.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 28 Apr 2011 20:07:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 2 May 2011 09:26:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-28"}
